{
  "texts": [
    "These architectures incorporate self-loops to effectively manage gradients over extended sequences, addressing the vanishing or exploding gradient issue.",
    "Recurrent Autoencoder is an autoencoder that incorporates recurrent layers, such as LSTM or GRU, within both the encoder and decoder components.",
    "Autoencoder (LSTMAE) (Nguyen et al. 2021) is an advanced variation of the recurrent autoencoder, specifically designed to capture representations from sequential data.",
    "In this architecture, both the encoder and decoder components are built using LSTM units, a type of recurrent layer.",
    "The encoder LSTM takes in a sequence of vectors, which can represent images or features."
  ]
}